00:30:56,621 --> 00:30:57,998
but instead I'm gonna thank you

495
00:30:58,056 --> 00:31:01,299
for not making me
wait another 11.

496
00:31:02,294 --> 00:31:04,399
Every little girl wants a pony

497
00:31:04,496 --> 00:31:06,373
until they have
to clean up after it.

498
00:31:06,465 --> 00:31:09,742
You think I'm gonna quit on this?
On an 11-year-old?

499
00:31:09,835 --> 00:31:12,145
The only relationship you haven't
quit on has been with me.

500
00:31:12,204 --> 00:31:14,707
Hmm. A needy,
truculent narcissist.

501
00:31:14,806 --> 00:31:17,980
I think it's been the perfect
training for parenthood.

502
00:31:19,244 --> 00:31:20,917
That's not even close.

503
00:31:22,481 --> 00:31:24,324
This is the rest of your life.

504
00:31:25,650 --> 00:31:27,857
If you screw this up,
you don't get to run away.

505
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:30,499
You get to ruin
both your lives.

506
00:31:30,589 --> 00:31:32,034
This is a bigger responsibility

507
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:35,663
than any you've ever taken
on, and screwed up.

508
00:31:37,829 --> 00:31:39,172
I know.

509
00:31:41,166 --> 00:31:42,941
That's why I'm so
excited about it.

510
00:31:51,443 --> 00:31:54,014
You're really happier doing this
than looking at boobs all day'?

511
00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:57,184
Luckily, I get patients like
you every now and again

512
00:31:57,282 --> 00:31:59,523
who let me
re-experience the joy.

513
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,028
You know the best
part of my day

514
00:32:03,088 --> 00:32:04,590
is when I'm sitting
in that penalty box

515
00:32:04,689 --> 00:32:07,295
after I beat someone up.

516
00:32:07,392 --> 00:32:10,737
It's the only time
I know I'm safe.

517
00:32:10,862 --> 00:32:12,933
Think Lemieux
ever felt that way?

518
00:32:13,031 --> 00:32:14,101
I'm not going back.

519
00:32:14,199 --> 00:32:15,200
To hockey?

520
00:32:15,300 --> 00:32:18,372
To enforcing.
Whatever that costs.

521
00:32:20,539 --> 00:32:21,779
Good for you.

522
00:32:21,873 --> 00:32:23,443
Oh!

523
00:32:23,542 --> 00:32:25,453
First goal for
the Pocket Rocket.

524
00:32:27,913 --> 00:32:29,392
Bobby?

525
00:32:32,417 --> 00:32:33,657
We need a team in here!

526
00:32:39,424 --> 00:32:43,236
He's completely paralyzed and he
tested negative for botulism.

527
00:32:47,999 --> 00:32:50,775
I am now accepting long shots.

528
00:32:52,103 --> 00:32:53,173
Polio?

529
00:32:53,271 --> 00:32:54,341
Some kids were
never vaccinated.

530
00:32:54,439 --> 00:32:57,909
Unless they played sports all their
lives and had two physicals a year.

531
00:32:58,743 --> 00:32:59,915
How about MLD?

532
00:32:59,978 --> 00:33:01,252
TAUB; That's a bad fit.

533
00:33:02,247 --> 00:33:04,158
I say that not because there's
no treatment for MLD,

534
00:33:04,249 --> 00:33:05,421
but because ifs a bad fit.

535
00:33:05,517 --> 00:33:07,087
His cognitive abilities
are unaffected.

536
00:33:07,519 --> 00:33:09,999
Prion disease could explain the
waxing and waning symptoms.

537
00:33:10,088 --> 00:33:11,590
The test for prions
is a brain biopsy.

538
00:33:11,690 --> 00:33:14,500
And given his history, there's
got to be brain swelling.

539
00:33:14,593 --> 00:33:16,698
We can't risk drilling
into his skull.

540
00:33:16,795 --> 00:33:17,933
Pretty sure we can.

541
00:33:18,029 --> 00:33:22,273
We also could keep talking until we can
find an answer we all can agree on.

542
00:33:22,767 --> 00:33:25,941
What, all of us? Those of us who
love him, those who hate him?

543
00:33:26,037 --> 00:33:28,017
Those who don't give
a crap about him or you?

544
00:33:28,106 --> 00:33:30,279
Or I could just discuss it
on my own with Foreman.

545
00:33:31,309 --> 00:33:32,549
He's not your friend.

546
00:33:32,644 --> 00:33:34,453
I get it' he's a patient.

547
00:33:34,546 --> 00:33:37,390
I'm not... He never
had your back.

548
00:33:38,483 --> 00:33:41,953
He didn't insist that
I apologize to you.

549
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:46,401
He asked me to take
you off the case.

550
00:33:53,632 --> 00:33:55,407
Biopsy his brain.

551
00:34:02,807 --> 00:34:03,842
Hey, Dad.

552
00:34:03,909 --> 00:34:04,910
He?'

553
00:34:05,677 --> 00:34:10,217
Sorry I'm late. Got in a fight
with my mom She is such a tool.

554
00:34:10,315 --> 00:34:11,692
I'm sure she means well.

555
00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:15,593
She wants to open a reserve in Costa
Rica for rescued birds of prey.

556
00:34:18,490 --> 00:34:19,901
But how serious is she?

557
00:34:19,991 --> 00:34:24,201
From my recollection, she used
to talk about doing a lot.

558
00:34:24,329 --> 00:34:27,333
Yeah, but she bought
plane tickets for Monday.

559
00:34:31,770 --> 00:34:36,014
Well, Costa Rica is beautiful.

560
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:38,179
And the schools are
supposed to be great.

561
00:34:38,276 --> 00:34:41,018
Oh! I'm not going. It's her
stupid dream, not mine.

562
00:34:41,947 --> 00:34:43,187
Then what will you do?

563
00:34:48,186 --> 00:34:49,358
Uh...

564
00:34:52,357 --> 00:34:56,100
I thought maybe
I could stay with you?

565
00:34:57,929 --> 00:35:00,466
Your place is only three
miles away from my school.

566
00:35:00,565 --> 00:35:01,805
I can bus it every day.

567
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:04,744
And I do my own laundry.
I keep my room tidy.

568
00:35:04,869 --> 00:35:07,975
Duncan, this...

569
00:35:08,073 --> 00:35:11,213
This is very sudden.

570
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:15,550
I know. I'm sorry.

571
00:35:19,784 --> 00:35:21,764
Please don't send me
to the jungle.

572
00:35:29,794 --> 00:35:32,138
If it's okay with your
mother, it's okay with me.

573
00:35:44,576 --> 00:35:46,283
Take me off the case.

574
00:35:47,812 --> 00:35:50,850
I've obviously completely
lost my objectivity.

575
00:35:50,949 --> 00:35:52,929
I'm not helping.
I'm not even neutral.

576
00:35:54,753 --> 00:35:56,096
Agreed.

577
00:35:57,088 --> 00:35:58,999
So why shouldn't
I take you off all my cases?

578
00:36:00,091 --> 00:36:02,093
Because you were right.
I hate bullies.

579
00:36:02,927 --> 00:36:03,997
You work for me.

580
00:36:04,095 --> 00:36:05,096
You're not a bully.

581
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:06,767
Pretty sure I am, dickwad.

582
00:36:06,831 --> 00:36:09,971
I've known a lot of bullies, people
who didn't like me because I'm short,

583
00:36:10,101 --> 00:36:11,171
people who didn't like me
because I'm Jewish.

584
00:36:11,269 --> 00:36:13,715
Yeah, I get it, there's a long
list of reasons not to like you.

585
00:36:13,805 --> 00:36:17,446
You relentlessly mock, but it's
not for self-aggrandizement,

586
00:36:17,509 --> 00:36:20,854
it's because ideas are
bigger than feelings.

587
00:36:22,781 --> 00:36:25,057
At least that's what
I choose to believe.

588
00:36:25,150 --> 00:36:29,121
I also thought you had the side
effect of desensitizing me.

589
00:36:33,458 --> 00:36:35,631
You little hebe.

590
00:36:36,961 --> 00:36:39,498
Here are some ideas for you.

591
00:36:39,631 --> 00:36:43,135
You screwed up. You kept on screwing up.
Everything you said is true.

592
00:36:44,302 --> 00:36:48,648
Except it doesn't mean
you walk away.

593
00:36:49,874 --> 00:36:52,821
You just learn
to trust nothing.

594
00:36:54,312 --> 00:36:58,351
Everything you think you feel,
everything you think you know,

595
00:36:59,184 --> 00:37:02,825
you question every call,
play through every whistle.

596
00:37:07,492 --> 00:37:09,563
I just had a light bulb.

597
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:11,836
Maybe.

598
00:37:12,530 --> 00:37:14,168
You can trust light bulbs.

599
00:37:24,542 --> 00:37:26,886
Stop.
It's not prions.

600
00:37:27,679 --> 00:37:31,684
Epstein-Barr gave him mono, it also
gave him Miller Fisher syndrome.

601
00:37:31,750 --> 00:37:34,754
The plasmapheresis
played through the whistle.

602
00:37:34,853 --> 00:37:37,800
We gave it to him for MPA, but when
he got worse, we took him off.

603
00:37:37,889 --> 00:37:40,392
When he got better, we thought
it was the antitoxin,

604
00:37:40,525 --> 00:37:43,369
but it was actually the
plasmapheresis still working.

605
00:37:43,895 --> 00:37:47,206
We had the right treatment,
just the wrong diagnosis.

606
00:37:48,366 --> 00:37:50,368
It was my metaphor
that solved the case.

607
00:37:51,202 --> 00:37:53,739
Put him back on plasmapheresis.
He'll be fine.

608
00:37:54,439 --> 00:37:56,282
Nice save.

609
00:37:56,374 --> 00:37:58,752
Didn't quite make up for being
a sieve the rest of the game.

610
00:38:08,052 --> 00:38:09,895
Ex-girlfriend's
baby again?

611
00:38:13,625 --> 00:38:15,605
His mother is moving
to Costa Rica,

612
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:17,640
he asked if he could
move in with me...

613
00:38:19,264 --> 00:38:20,800
and I said yes.

614
00:38:26,905 --> 00:38:30,910
Well, it's only
six or seven years.

615
00:38:31,943 --> 00:38:33,581
Unless he can't
get into college,

616
00:38:33,645 --> 00:38:36,148
in which case it's more a
matter of your life expectancy.

617
00:38:36,247 --> 00:38:39,660
I said yes, knowing I'm not
remotely ready for that,

618
00:38:39,751 --> 00:38:43,198
knowing he's not ready to be
separated from his mother.

619
00:38:43,288 --> 00:38:46,030
This isn't the act of
a mature, rational adult.

620
00:38:49,627 --> 00:38:51,300
I can't do this, House.

621
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:54,969
You were right.

622
00:38:58,169 --> 00:39:02,015
I have an idea that can make
this entire problem go away.

623
00:39:02,106 --> 00:39:05,644
Yes, I really want to hear your
clever late-term abortion joke.

624
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:08,350
You were right about everything.
This is life.

625
00:39:08,446 --> 00:39:11,052
It's real.
It doesn't just go away.

626
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:18,394
None of that is true.

627
00:39:23,962 --> 00:39:25,236
He?'

628
00:39:25,330 --> 00:39:26,400
Duncan.

629
00:39:27,165 --> 00:39:31,170
Actually, it's Wendel, one "L".

630
00:39:33,905 --> 00:39:38,411
If you're gonna get pissy,
remember, it was House's idea.

631
00:39:43,648 --> 00:39:44,718
You're an actor?

632
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:47,856
Five commercials, and a
recurring on Days of our Lives.

633
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:56,561
You were regretting not having
kids, so I gave you one.

634
00:39:57,362 --> 00:40:01,174
Thereby rendering you regret-free.
It's a priceless gift.

635
00:40:01,232 --> 00:40:02,677
Get out.
Well, it's not priceless.

636
00:40:02,734 --> 00:40:04,509
He charges SAG minimum...

637
00:40:04,569 --> 00:40:06,412
Get out!

638
00:40:08,907 --> 00:40:10,511
Chillax, Dad.

639
00:40:11,175 --> 00:40:13,621
Can you do an Australian accent?

640
00:40:40,371 --> 00:40:42,544
I just got the call.

641
00:40:43,541 --> 00:40:46,454
Three-year deal,
2.1 million.

642
00:40:54,385 --> 00:40:58,390
What about the flooded backyard
and pretending to be Lemieux'?

643
00:40:59,390 --> 00:41:01,301
That's why I took it.

644
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:04,902
After all I did to get here,

645
00:41:04,963 --> 00:41:07,341
half a dream is
better than nothing.

646
00:41:10,068 --> 00:41:13,982
Maybe my new coach will see
what my Juniors coach didn't.

647
00:41:17,675 --> 00:41:19,018
That'd be nice.

648
00:41:41,866 --> 00:41:43,277
I'm not sleeping with you.

649
00:41:45,169 --> 00:41:46,705
That's a shame.

650
00:41:52,710 --> 00:41:54,121
This is about Popo.

651
00:41:55,813 --> 00:41:59,226
She's not sleeping
with me either, right?

652
00:41:59,317 --> 00:42:02,127
You were jealous
of me, my family.

653
00:42:10,628 --> 00:42:14,075
Maybe you've got too much
and I've got too little.

654
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,382
I might sleep
with you after all.

655
00:42:56,541 --> 00:42:59,021
The woman that I called,
that was really Beth?

656
00:42:59,610 --> 00:43:01,612
Found her on Facebook.

657
00:43:01,712 --> 00:43:03,089
How much did she charge?

658
00:43:03,181 --> 00:43:05,752
Nothing. She's still
pissed at you.

659
00:43:07,618 --> 00:43:09,063
<i>Can you pass the bacon?</i>

660
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,361
I thought you liked prosciutto.

661
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:13,424
Nobody likes prosciutto.

